sub_title: Senior Consultant | Data Scientist | Photographer | Tour Leader
summary:
Driven by the potential impact on society using data, I do consultancy in Data Science, specializing in Natural Language Processing, Computer Vision, Python, SQL, Azure and PowerBi. 

I also have a background in Civil Engineering, Water Resources Management and Cultural Anthropology. During my early career I worked in development and humanitarian aid in Africa and Asia as a Water, Sanitation & Hygiene (WASH) expert for the Red Cross and the UN. 

In my free time I enjoy being a tour leader for an adventurous and sustainable travel agency. Sharing and facilitating unforgettable experiences gives me energy. The primary region I cover was Latin America, now shifting to North America. Hiking is one of my favorite activities.

Occasionally I take up photography initiatives like creating social media content for world water day for UNHCR, making low key portrets and more.

My signature is the combination of my analytical skills with my open-mind. I thrive when taking up challenges and above all delivering results that matter.
